&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Twitch, Content Accounting is responsible for managing the end to end financial and reporting obligations of negotiated agreements with content providers, influencers, production companies, and music rights holders. Our goal is to close our books in accordance with U.S. GAAP &amp;amp; internal accounting policy and meet our contractually obligated payout and reporting requirements. We support a diverse set of business stakeholders including content acquisition, music licensing, influencer marketing, and event production. We work closely with our legal, FP&amp;amp;A, tax and enterprise technology counterparts to accelerate Twitch’s strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Senior Accountant eager to help us re-imagine how Content Accounting operates with the growing capabilities of AI. Your core work will have you involved at every step of the process from contract ideation through to final payout—providing support for negotiation, drafting technical accounting memos, preparing cost and payout calculations, executing month-end close activities, facilitating payment runs, and delivering reporting.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A successful candidate uses GenAI tools both reflexively and responsibly to enhance the group&#39;s daily productivity. You are passionate about accounting, thrive in the details, have an understanding of how data flows through systems, and have demonstrated the ability to break down ambiguous problems into concrete steps. You will play a key role in standardizing data and modifying processes, both inside and outside our team, to enable the introduction of GenAI to drive value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role reports to the Director of Content Accounting. You can work in San Francisco, CA; Los Angeles, CA; Irvine, CA; or Seattle, WA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the completeness of contractual records, review contract terms and document the application of our accounting policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support month-end close including preparing journal entries, reconciliations, and fluctuation narratives for content costs&lt;/li&

